{"lemma":"فُراتِ","slug":"فُراتِ","root":"ف.ر.ت","root_slug":"ف-ر-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فُرات","root":"فرت","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33353"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8F%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33353","headword_ar":"فُرَاتٌ","root":"frt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to water, (T, S, M, &c.,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaAhN","text_ar":"فُرَاهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", both chaste forms, and well known, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbuwtN","text_ar":"تَابُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbuwhN","text_ar":"تَابُوهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Towsheeh, MF, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sweet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very sweet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sweetest kind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that subdues thirst by its excessive sweetness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xxv. 55:) so called, accord. to Z, because it breaks the vehemence of thirst, and allays it; as though from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafata","text_ar":"رَفَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and formed by transposition: (TA:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N furaAtN","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ فُرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, O, K,) and in a copy of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firaAtN","text_ar":"فِرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miyaAhN furaAtN","text_ar":"مِيَاهٌ فُرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, O, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firotaAnN","text_ar":"فِرْتَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, in copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furotaAnN","text_ar":"فُرْتَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farotaAnN","text_ar":"فَرْتَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"girobaAnN","text_ar":"غِرْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guraAbN","text_ar":"غُرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaAtN","text_ar":"فُرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pluralized, but this is rarely the case. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuraAtu","text_ar":"الفُرَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Euphrates;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the river of ElKoofeh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, * K; *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great, celebrated river, which issues from the limits of Er-Room, then passes by the borders of Syria &c., and, after meeting with the Tigris, forms therewith one river, and pours forth into the Sea"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gulf"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Persia."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuraAtaAni","text_ar":"الفُرَاتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation applied to ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Euphrates and Tigris;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuraAtu","text_ar":"الفُرَاتُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dijolapu","text_ar":"دِجْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to the S [and O]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuraAtu","text_ar":"الفُرَاتُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dujayolN","text_ar":"دُجَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Euphrates and Dujeyl,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which latter is a branch of the Tigris]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sea:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) so in a verse of Aboo-Dhu-eyb describing pearls as found therein. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","T","M","L","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}